\begin{enumerate}
  \item Highlight of the week
\end{enumerate}

\paragraph{Alma 1:30--31.}
When the people of the church shared
shared their wealth with the poor,
``they did prosper''.  (``Prosper''
means they got lots of blessings.)

\paragraph{Alma 4:11}
When the people of the church shared
shared their wealth with the poor,
they brought ``the destruction of
the people''.

\paragraph{Example.}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Print out paper play money.
  \item Have candy (from the bishop!) to sell for the play money.
    Use a random number to distribute?
    Have four dollaroos.
\end{itemize}

\paragraph{Song.}
``Jesus Said Love Everyone''


